.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\f(CW\*(C`DBIx::Class::Helper::Schema::Verifier::RelationshipColumnName\*(C'\fR verifies that
none of your columns have the same name as a relationship.  If you create a
relationship that has the same name as a column, to access the column you will
be forced to use \f(CW\*(C`get_column\*(C'\fR, additionally it is just confusing having them
be the same name.  What I tend to do is define the columns to be something like
\&\f(CW\*(C`user_id\*(C'\fR and have the relationship then be simply \f(CW\*(C`user\*(C'\fR.
